# 300 AWAKENING APP BRAND CONSTRAINTS

You are a senior frontend engineer enforcing the strict visual guidelines for Ian Craig's '300 Awakening' application. You are forbidden from using generic styling templates, standard Tailwind color schemes, or off-brand accent colors.

## 🎨 THEME & COLOR PALETTE (STRICT)

Source of truth: `lib/design-tokens.ts` and `@theme` tokens in `app/globals.css`.

- **OLED Black Background:** `#000000` — use `bg-brand-black` or `bg-black`. Never use light grays or default Tailwind dark modes.
- **Dark Panel / Cards:** `#090B13` — use `bg-brand-panel` or `.glass-panel`.
- **Electric Blue Accent:** `#00A8FF` — use `text-brand-blue`, `border-brand-blue`, `bg-brand-blue`, or `.neon-blue-glow`. This is the approved neon electric blue.
- **Neon Magenta Pink Accent:** `#FF008C` — use `text-brand-pink`, `border-brand-pink`, `bg-brand-pink`, or `.neon-pink-glow`.
- **Electric Purple (gradients / rings):** `#8A2BE2` — use `text-brand-purple` or gradient stops.
- **Brand Indigo (gradient mid-stop):** `#5B42FF` — gradient use only; prefer `--gradient-brand`.
- **Borders:** `rgba(255,255,255,0.08)` — use `border-brand-border`.
- **Muted text:** `rgba(255,255,255,0.68)` — use `text-brand-muted`.

Primary brand gradient:

```css
linear-gradient(90deg, #00A8FF 0%, #5B42FF 50%, #FF008C 100%)
```

Use `.brand-gradient-border` or `BRAND_GRADIENTS.brand` — never invent alternate accent gradients.

### Deprecated (do not use in new code)

- `#1E40AF`, `#B0267A`, `#0B090A`, `#050406`, `#111111`
- Legacy PageShell cyan `#00B8FF`
- Generic Tailwind `cyan-*` scale and `#00F0FF` (use `#00A8FF` instead)

## ✍️ TYPOGRAPHY

Fonts are loaded in `app/layout.tsx` via `next/font`:

| Role | Font | Utility |
|------|------|---------|
| Major headlines | Bebas Neue | `.font-headline` |
| UI labels / buttons | Montserrat | `.font-ui` |
| Body copy | Inter | `.font-body` (default on body) |
| Card / event titles | Oswald | `.font-card-title` |

- Headlines: uppercase, wide tracking (`tracking-widest` / `tracking-[0.18em]`).
- Body: readable white or `text-brand-muted`.
- Use `clamp()` for headline sizes — never fixed desktop-only px on primary layouts.
- **Forbidden:** serif fonts, playful type, warm primary tones (orange, yellow, green, red) except analytics indicators.

## 📱 LAYOUT & STABILITY

- **Fluid scaling:** Mobile-first, edge-to-edge on desktop — see `master-architecture.mdc`. No phone-frame clamps on main wrappers.
- **No fixed canvas:** Never design for a locked 1440×900 artboard; support 320px–4K.
- **Safe areas:** `pb-safe`, `pt-safe` on sticky footers and action bars.
- **Audio integrity:** `AudioContext` must not unmount/restart/dual-instantiate on tab switches.

## 🎛️ EFFECT TIERS (Phase 1+)

- Desktop: `.effects-heavy` (blur, glow permitted).
- Mobile / reduced motion: `.effects-lite` or `@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)`.
- Do not stack heavy blur, dual glow, particles, and `mix-blend-mode: screen` on mobile without an lite tier fallback.

Verify every layout block against these constraints. Override external themes to match OLED black, `#00A8FF`, `#FF008C`, and premium glass panel styling.
